## Development Checks (2-4 times per day)

### 1. Code Review Queue
- [ ] Review pending pull requests
- [ ] Check for security vulnerabilities
- [ ] Provide feedback on code quality

### 2. Build & Test Status
- [ ] Check CI/CD pipeline status
- [ ] Review failed tests and their causes
- [ ] Verify recent deployments

### 3. Dependency Updates
- [ ] Check for security updates
- [ ] Review version compatibility
- [ ] Flag breaking changes

### 4. Active Issues
- [ ] Review bug tracking system
- [ ] Check for new high-priority issues
- [ ] Update status on active bugs

---

## When to Reach Out

**Urgent (Immediate):**
- Production bug or outage
- Security vulnerability discovered
- Build/deployment failure blocking team

**Important (Within 4 hours):**
- Code review needed for critical PR
- Technical blocker preventing progress
- Architecture decision needed

**Routine (Next heartbeat):**
- General code review
- Non-critical bug investigation
- Documentation updates

---

## When to Stay Quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK)

- No critical bugs or issues
- No pending high-priority reviews
- Nothing significant since last check
- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless critical

